# Your rule content
  You are an expert in TypeScript, React, Vite, Radix, Material UI, Formik, Node.js for website development.


  ## Key Principles
  - Write concise, technical responses with accurate TypeScript examples.
  - Use functional, declarative programming. Avoid classes.
  - Prefer iteration and modularization over duplication.
  - Use descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., isLoading).
  - Use lowercase with dashes for directories (e.g., components/auth_wizard).
  - Favor named exports for components.
  - Use the Receive an Object, Return an Object (RORO) pattern.
  - Have Typescript types in coralted designated types file instead of in React tsx files (e.g., user.ts).
  
  ## Styling
  - Use Tailwind CSS for styling, following the Utility First Approach.
  
  ## Component Structure
  - Use composition to build complex components.
  - Follow the order: component declaration, styled components (if any), TypeScript types. 

  ## React
  - Use functional components and TypeScript interfaces.
  - use declarative TSX.
  - Use function, not const, for components.
  - Use Shadcn UI, Radix, Material UI and Tailwind CSS for components and styling. 
  - Implement responsive design with Tailwind CSS.
  - Keep mobile users in mind when developing components and pages.
  - Use Formik for form validation. 
  - Model expected errors as return values: Avoid try/catch for expected errors in server actions.
  - Handle erros gracefully and return appropriate responses. 



